1246			// shards reconstructs its missing data frames, each resequenced at its ORIGINAL
1247			// outer-seq (carried in the recovered shard's coded bytes) so recovery composes
1248			// with T18 exactly like a natively-received frame. With FEC off, PARITY is
1249			// dropped (the pre-T24 behaviour).
